#Text=Libya and Switzerland to meet about visa bans
#Text=Thursday , February 18 , 2010
#Text=Map of Schengen nations ██Full Schengen EU members

#Text=Libya and Switzerland have reportedly agreed to meet in an effort to resolve a diplomatic row about travel visas .
#Text=Micheline Calmy-Rey of Switzerland and Moussa Koussa of Libya will meet in the presence of Miguel Ángel Moratinos of Spain .
#Text=All three are the heads of foreign relations for their respective countries .
#Text=The meeting comes at the urging of Malta and Italy .
#Text=Libya announced on Tuesday that it has suspended and/or revoked visas given to citizens of the Schengen Area of Europe .
#Text=Four Italian citizens have been detained at the Tripoli International Airport pending deportation , as their visas have been revoked .
#Text=Confirming the situation , a Libyan official told Reuters :
